{"action":"created","comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/LinearAlgebra.jl/pulls/comments/1894601355","pull_request_review_id":2518627061,"id":1894601355,"node_id":"PRRC_kwDONPNfxc5w7VKL","diff_hunk":"@@ -1024,8 +1024,8 @@ function svd(D::Diagonal{T}) where {T<:Number}
     Vt = copy(U)
     for i in 1:length(d)
         j = piv[i]
-        U[j,i] = d[j] / S[i]
-        Vt[i,j] = one(Td)
+        U[j,i] = iszero(d[j]) ? oneunit(Td) : d[j] / S[i]","path":"src/diagonal.jl","commit_id":"bb5f566534c669c88a804fb38e6a9997fffa4d2d","original_commit_id":"bb5f566534c669c88a804fb38e6a9997fffa4d2d","user":{"login":"dkarrasch","id":26658441,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2NjU4NDQx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26658441?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch","html_url":"https://github.com/dkarrasch","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dkarrasch/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"> That's what I would have thought. But the `eltype` of `V` and `U` is really `oneunit(Td)`, not `one(Td)`. Furthermore, this is explicitly tested for [here](https://github.com/JuliaLang/LinearAlgebra.jl/blob/bb5f566534c669c88a804fb38e6a9997fffa4d2d/test/diagonal.jl#L481).

I think I touched this method last. The eltype is `Td`, which is ideally "unitless" (`oneunit(T)/oneunit(T)`). I just had no better idea of how to strip the unit. Currently, this works in the tests by promoting unitless numbers to the unitless version of the "unitful" type `Furlong{0}`.

