```julia
julia> using LinearAlgebra

julia> A = zeros(200,0); B = Bidiagonal(zeros(0), zeros(0), :U); C = similar(A);

julia> @btime mul!($C, $A, $B);
  83.690 ns (4 allocations: 160 bytes) # nightly
  15.408 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes) # This PR
```
Currently, the matrix multiplication functions involving `Bidiagonal` matrices materialize small matrices (likely to handle such cases painlessly), and this PR avoids any such allocation if the arrays are empty. 
